To our knowledge, no structural or functional studies have addressed the involvement of the cholinergic output structures of the midbrain in hallucinating demented and non-demented PD patients [PD(D)] and DLB patients
Therefore, the aim of the present retrospective study was to investigate the PPN region and one of its projection areas, the thalamus, by means of voxel-based morphometry in these patients.
